				<h1>''Frost To-Night''</h1>
				
				<p class="book-page-author"><a href="https://librivox.org/author/8092">Edith M. Thomas <span class="dod-dob">(1854 - 1925)</span></a></p>
				
				<p class="description">Edith Matilda Thomas (August 12, 1854 – September 13, 1925) was an American poet who "was one of the first poets to capture successfully the excitement of the modern city."<br />This poem taken from the The Little Book of Modern Verse.  1917.; Jessie B. Rittenhouse, ed. (1869–1948) - Summary by Wikipedia</p>

				<p class="book-page-genre"><span>Genre(s):</span> Multi-version (Weekly and Fortnightly poetry)</p>

				<p class="book-page-genre"><span>Language:</span> English</p>
				
								<p class="book-page-genre primary_keywords_string"><span>Keyword(s):</span> <a href="https://librivox.org/keywords/32">nature</a> (913), reaping (1)</p>
								
								</p>
				
